The key insight is that after an update:
- If the local field is positive, the spin becomes +1 (up)
- If the local field is negative, the spin becomes -1 (down)
- If the local field is zero, the spin stays the same

In all cases, the spin change times the local field is non-negative, so the energy difference (which is the negative of this product) is non-positive.

